race.comment: BETTY'S GARDEN (6) recorded a nose win (28.83) in a Grade 4/5 last time at Sale. Boasts a top strike-rate from this draw, winning three of five runs. With a clean break looks hard to beat. AUSSIE MOSS (1) showed strong early pace and proved too slick around Sandown over 515m in 29.61, claiming a Mix 6/7 by 2.25 lengths. The form from his last run is stacking up nicely. One of the prime contenders. WINNING RATIO (8) ran below best last time finishing sixth (26.44) over 460m at Geelong from Box 4. Has ability and is one of the better chances. CLONCURRY GOLD (2) can find the frame without surprising.
